################################################################################
# SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS: Survey-weighted Restricted Cubic Splines with
# multiply imputed data
#
# PURPOSE:
# - Merge PHQ9_depression_above_10 from 2.data_phq8.rds into each imputed
#   dataset from 13.PHQ8_MI_scored_datasets_list_v2.rds
# - Use PHQ-9 >= 10 as the sensitivity-analysis outcome
# - Fit survey-weighted RCS logistic regression models with MI pooling
# - Estimate overall association and non-linearity (Wald tests)
# - Derive pooled nadir and risk-escalation point from Model 4 spline curve
# - Perform secondary analysis using the RCS-derived categorized exposure
# - Export Supplementary Figure G in TIFF / PDF / PNG
#
# COLOR:  #0072B2  (Okabe-Ito blue — colorblind-safe, distinct from Figure F)
# PANEL LABEL: G
#
# NOTES:
# - Observational, cross-sectional analysis. No causal language.
# - P-values from MI-pooled Wald tests.
################################################################################

